18/10/2006
LUXEMBOURG -- Meeting on Tuesday (October 17th), the EU Council endorsed the scheduled accession of Bulgaria and Romania on January 1st, as recommended in the latest report by the European Commission (EC). The statement praised the two countries for reforms implemented thus far and urged them to press ahead with a number of others. The EU foreign ministers also voiced support for EC plans to monitor their performance in areas such as judicial reform and the fight against crime and corruption. (EU website, BNR, Rompres, Reuters, UPI - 17/10/06)
